# Walkthrough — LoRA/QLoRA VLM Finetuning Pipeline

## What Was Built

A **single-file finetuning pipeline** ([finetune/finetune_qwen_vlm.py](file:///c:/Dev/Internship/GOVT-DOC-VLM/finetune/finetune_qwen_vlm.py), ~700 lines) supporting both Qwen3.5-VL model variants on A100 80GB. The existing inference pipeline is **completely untouched**.

### New Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [finetune_qwen_vlm.py](file:///c:/Dev/Internship/GOVT-DOC-VLM/finetune/finetune_qwen_vlm.py) | Full pipeline: data loading → model loading → LoRA config → training → evaluation |
| [requirements_finetune.txt](file:///c:/Dev/Internship/GOVT-DOC-VLM/finetune/requirements_finetune.txt) | GPU-only dependencies (peft, bitsandbytes, etc.) |
| [example_data.jsonl](file:///c:/Dev/Internship/GOVT-DOC-VLM/finetune/example_data.jsonl) | Schema reference with 2 sample entries |

### Modified Files
**None.** Existing `doc-qwen3.5-27b/` and `doc-qwen3.5-122b-a10b/` directories are unchanged.

---

## Code Review Summary

### § 1 — Data Loading & Preprocessing
- [DocumentAugmentor](file:///c:/Dev/Internship/GOVT-DOC-VLM/finetune/finetune_qwen_vlm.py#120-196): perspective warp, blur, brightness/contrast jitter — targets scan quality variance
- [GovtDocDataset](file:///c:/Dev/Internship/GOVT-DOC-VLM/finetune/finetune_qwen_vlm.py#218-342): JSONL loader → PIL image + Qwen processor tokenization, prompt tokens masked to -100
- [MultimodalDataCollator](file:///c:/Dev/Internship/GOVT-DOC-VLM/finetune/finetune_qwen_vlm.py#344-431): left-pads text (causal LM convention), stacks/pads variable-size pixel_values

### § 2 — Model Loading & Quantization
- **27B**: `torch.bfloat16`, no quantization — fits A100 at ~74GB (tight but workable)
- **122B MoE**: NF4 4-bit + double quant via `BitsAndBytesConfig`, gate/router modules excluded from quantization (`llm_int8_skip_modules=["gate"]`) AND frozen (`requires_grad=False`)
- **Layer freezing**: bottom 75% of decoder layers frozen, MLPs frozen across all layers

### § 3 — LoRA Configuration
- **Target modules**: `q_proj, k_proj, v_proj, o_proj, visual` — all attention + vision encoder
- **Rank 64** (not 16) — justified by vision-heavy spatial feature learning
- **Alpha 128** (ratio=2), dropout 0.05, no bias training
- MoE gate explicitly excluded from LoRA targets

### § 4 — Training Loop
- Gradient checkpointing: always on
- Optimizer: `paged_adamw_8bit` — saves ~8GB on 122B
- [VRAMProfilerCallback](file:///c:/Dev/Internship/GOVT-DOC-VLM/finetune/finetune_qwen_vlm.py#618-655): logs memory every 25 steps, warns at 95% utilization
- [GradientNormCallback](file:///c:/Dev/Internship/GOVT-DOC-VLM/finetune/finetune_qwen_vlm.py#657-694) (MoE only): detects gradient spikes > 5x running average

### § 5 — Evaluation
Three domain-specific metrics (not just loss):

| Metric | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| **CER** | Catches single-char errors in amounts/dates — more granular than WER |
| **Field F1** | Precision/recall on extracted key:value pairs |
| **Table Cell Accuracy** | Per-cell exact match — surfaces errors clustering in numeric columns |

